metadata.name: Mandatory Destiny #45
metadata.description:
"Mandatory Destiny" is the fifth collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

It is impossible for everyone to be equal. Too much of a person is defined by random chance. The country they were born in, the financial situation of their family, even their genetics. If someone was unlucky and has low natural IQ, they can't change it. And it affects their life significantly. If someone was born in a poor country or family, it might be extremely harder to get a good education, and later, a well-paying job. Some people are fortunate enough to get a headstart, while others aren't so lucky.

The only way for everyone to be truly equal would be identical starting conditions, and that's utterly impossible to achieve.

metadata.name: fx(Punk) #250
metadata.description: fx(Punk) is a .png layered illustration of the Punks which uses PureSpider pfp master code to generate randomized iterations.

Witness hundreds of small geometric objects gather under one roof to create a cosmic rain!

Ever since I was a child, I have always been good with geometric objects. I used to draw objects such as cubes, cylinders and prisms on paper for hours. As if I'm getting lost in every line between those geometric objects! In this way, every detail of geometry in my daily life and in my other existing life attracts my attention.

Recently, I have been doing research on colors and color palettes, it is really impressive how thousands of color mixtures affect each other and the psychology of living things!

解depending on the screen size you can get different resolutions, which brings out a different side of the project! so you can run this project on all screen sizes and get the output!解

Key:
- Press "s" to export an PNG image


Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Coded Tiny Dinos #186
metadata.description:
Coded Tiny Dinos.

Inspired from Tiny Dinos collection which are cc0 (copyright waived), they are pfp with layered images.

Coded Tiny Dinos do not use any form of images, they are fully made with code, making them layers free pfp image made just with code and generated based on the hash.

You can check the code for yourself.

(I have asked the moderation team if i can publish this project, they said yes on a condition i mention everything in the description)

metadata.description:
Portfolio - Cities, 1970-1980: City 1972

metadata.name: Nevercolliding Circles #49
metadata.description:
A beautiful cluster of circles that never touch

Realized in Vanilla JS with a sprinkle of CSS

This piece and "Tangent Circles" started from my d/24732 on Dwitter, then I focused more on the style leaving behind the 140 chars limit...

metadata.name: Microgravity #1025
metadata.description:
Microgravity is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

Scale symmetry of abstract semiliquid forms.

Click on a section of the image to explore deeper.
- Use keys [0-9] to change the detail level.
- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "R" key to reset the coordinates.
